\series bold
\emph on
objective function
\series default
 
\emph default
or 
\series bold
\emph on
cost function
\series default
\emph default
.
 The variables in the vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{x}$
\end_inset

 is referred to as 
\series bold
\emph on
decision variables
\series default
\emph default
.
 The set 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset

 is called the 
\series bold
\emph on
constraint set
\series default
 
\emph default
or 
\series bold
\emph on
feasible set
\series default
\emph default
.
 The vector that minimizes 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

 over 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset

 is called the 
\emph on
minimizer
\emph default
, in the case of maximizing 
\begin_inset Formula $f$
\end_inset

, it is called the 
\emph on
maximizer 
\emph default
and together they are called 
\emph on
extremizer.

\emph default
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega=\mathbb{\mathbb{R}}^{n}$
\end_inset

, the problem is referred to as an 
\emph on
unconstrained optimization problem
\emph default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The above formulation gives constraint over a set, called 
\emph on
set constraint.
 
\emph default
If 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset

